                  </persName>
             MASON (Police-constable G 214.) I was in the watch-house, and heard an alarm; I ran out, and stopped the prisoner; I saw this handkerchief hanging from the bottom of the tail of his coat, and it fell from him.(Property produced and sworn to.)</p>
               <p>Prisoner's Defence. I saw a young man drop it - I took it up, and ran after him.</p>
